      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The eastbound North Coast Linn\ntied on the Northern Pacific, due to\narrive here yesterday morning at\n1910, was ditched at Paha, small\nstation between Lind and Ritzville.\nFive coaches were derailed but no\none except a man who was beating\nthe blind baggage was hurt serious\nly. The wreck was a result of a\ntrestle giving way under the rear\ntruck of the engine. The track in\nthat vicinity is again becoming\nweak as result of the wet\nweather."
    }
